00:48:38,936 --> 00:48:43,237
And I think the last time we reported on this, if I'm remembering correctly, was on December 7th.

496
00:48:43,777 --> 00:48:55,560
And on that meeting, we referred back to some guidance that the administration put out in late October, early November, which was guidance that we developed in consultation with our largest bargaining partner, the Teachers Union.

497
00:48:55,580 --> 00:49:00,721
What we said at the time was that the type of additional support

498
00:49:01,425 --> 00:49:04,427
has to be individualized to the situation.

499
00:49:04,808 --> 00:49:12,894
So sometimes that will mean additional after-school hours, which a number of schools have provided, and teachers have been very cooperative in supporting us in.

500
00:49:13,354 --> 00:49:17,717
Other times it's been with concurrent instruction in a virtual environment.

501
00:49:18,258 --> 00:49:28,285
And the sort of three prongs that we said that each situation should be reviewed under is what is the grade level, what is the content area, what is the particular lesson.

502
00:49:28,926 --> 00:49:29,046
And

503
00:49:29,891 --> 00:49:43,482
We continue to encourage administrators to work with teachers and to make sure that each of their classrooms in their school and each of the programs in their school are being looked at on a case-by-case basis to see how we can best provide that additional support.

504
00:49:43,983 --> 00:49:53,610
I think in addition to that, we're going to need to roll out a variety of acceleration and remedial support measures in the spring using the ESSER funding.

505
00:49:54,131 --> 00:49:58,094
And in doing that, my hope is that we're able to bridge those gaps even further.

506
00:49:59,048 --> 00:50:11,828
All that being said, this is a huge disruption to students education and the continuity of instruction and that disruption has a disproportionate impact on some of our more vulnerable learners.

507
00:50:12,287 --> 00:50:25,882
We know that and that's something that it is going to be incumbent upon us to be highly vigilant, both this school year during the summer and beyond to make sure that these students educational careers are not defined entirely by this disruption.

508
00:50:26,263 --> 00:50:33,771
So I say that only to say, like, we're providing a lot of support and I think we're being very innovative and we're being very vigilant about the work that needs to be done.

509
00:50:34,813 --> 00:50:39,956
we should not in any way underestimate the scale of the challenge that is before us.

510
00:50:40,097 --> 00:50:49,743
And it gets worse each time we have to send students out, which again, the way to avoid that in many cases is to get vaccinated.

511
00:50:50,263 --> 00:50:54,886
And which is why, well, I understand that this is a message that is received differently in different corners.

512
00:50:55,587 --> 00:51:02,872
It is the position of the district that the best way to bring this chapter in our history to a close is for everyone to get vaccinated.

